        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 30 at 8:18AM CDT until July 30 at 8:30AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 816 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Elvaston
moving east at 25 mph. Quarter size hail was reported on the
northwest side of Keokuk with this storm.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Carthage, Hamilton, Ferris, Burnside, Adrian, Elvaston, and Basco.
</description>
        <instruction>Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
